<p>I am writing a script for an <strong>Alfred</strong> workflow. However, the string comparison never evaluates true. </p>  <p>The <code>"{query}"</code> inside the script does get replaced with a correct <code>ctext</code> value type which I can obverse using <code>display dialog "{query}"</code> and <code>display dialog class of "{query}"</code>.</p>  <pre><code>if "{query}" is equal to "a" then     say "in the a case" else     say "in the else case" end if </code></pre>  <p>I have also tried use <code>if "{query}" = "a" then</code> but still have the same outcome.</p>  <p>The evaluation keeps falling to the <code>else</code> statement.</p>  <p>I am referring the article below when writing the conditional statements.</p>  <p><a href="http://computers.tutsplus.com/tutorials/if-and-if-else-applescript-conditional-statements--mac-45590" rel="nofollow">http://computers.tutsplus.com/tutorials/if-and-if-else-applescript-conditional-statements--mac-45590</a></p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/8Dl8Z.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/8Dl8Z.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>